Chapter 1: Integers

Introduction to Integers

Integers are a number system that includes positive numbers, negative numbers, and zero. They are whole numbers without any fractional or decimal parts. The set of integers is represented by the letter 'Z' or 'I' and can be written as:

Z = {..., -4, -3, -2, -1, 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, ...}

  • Positive Integers: These are the natural numbers, also known as counting numbers (1, 2, 3, 4, ...).
  • Negative Integers: These are the opposites of the positive integers (..., -4, -3, -2, -1).
  • Zero: Zero is an integer that is neither positive nor negative.

Integers on the Number Line

A number line is a visual representation of integers.

  • Adding a positive integer means moving to the right.
  • Adding a negative integer means moving to the left.
  • Subtracting a positive integer means moving to the left.
  • Subtracting a negative integer means moving to the right.

Properties of Integers

Properties of Addition

  • Closure Property: The sum of any two integers is always an integer.
  • Commutative Property: a + b = b + a
  • Associative Property: (a + b) + c = a + (b + c)
  • Additive Identity: a + 0 = a
  • Additive Inverse: a + (-a) = 0

Properties of Multiplication

  • Closure Property: The product of any two integers is always an integer.
  • Commutative Property: a × b = b × a
  • Associative Property: (a × b) × c = a × (b × c)
  • Multiplicative Identity: a × 1 = a
  • Multiplication by Zero: a × 0 = 0

Distributive Property

  • Distributivity of Multiplication over Addition: a × (b + c) = (a × b) + (a × c)
  • Distributivity of Multiplication over Subtraction: a × (b - c) = a × b - a × c

Operations with Integers

Addition

  • Same Signs: Add their absolute values and keep the common sign.
  • Different Signs: Subtract the smaller absolute value from the larger absolute value and keep the sign of the integer with the larger absolute value.

Subtraction

To subtract an integer, you can add its additive inverse. For example, a - b is the same as a + (-b).

Multiplication

  • Same Signs: The product of two positive integers or two negative integers is a positive integer.
  • Different Signs: The product of a positive integer and a negative integer is a negative integer.

Division

  • Division is the inverse operation of multiplication.
  • Division of any integer by zero is not defined.
  • Any integer divided by 1 gives the same integer.
  • Signs in Division:
    • (-) ÷ (+) = (-)
    • (+) ÷ (-) = (-)
    • (-) ÷ (-) = (+)
  • Integers are not closed under division.
); }; export default IntegersNotes;
